questions.question:
Consider the following measures India is contemplating to enhance its engagement via multilateral development bank (MDB) regional offices in Africa:
(a) Establishing permanent liaison desks or colocated staff with MDB regional offices in strategic corridors;
(b) Using regional offices as conveners for integrated dialogues that align diplomatic, development and security tools across Ministries (External Affairs, Defence, Commerce) and EXIM Bank;
(c) Centralising all operational decision‑making in New Delhi to minimise local variability. 
Which of the following is/are most consistent with the cluster's recommendations?
